This paper discusses load balancing in data centers, content delivery networks, and mobile networks, which are all related to network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the impact on end-users' experience, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). However, since the focus is on the technical aspects of load balancing, cs.HC is less likely. The paper also mentions memory consumption and denial of service attacks, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper proposes a new load balancing solution, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.PF (Performance). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.SY, and cs.PF.
